[[File:Columbus, Ohio (2018) - 025.jpg|thumb|300px|The statues in [[Battelle Riverfront Park]], 2018]] The '''James W. Barney Pickaweekee Story Grove''' features a series of [[bronze sculptures]] by Jack Greaves, installed in [[Columbus, Ohio]]'s [[Battelle Riverfront Park]], in the United States. The artworks, completed in 1992, were inspired by S. J. Seaburn's story, ''Pickaweekee, A Myth of Discovery''.<ref name="Darbee">{{cite news |last1=Darbee |first1=Jeff |title=City Quotient: The Scioto’s Storybook Statues |url=http://www.columbusmonthly.com/lifestyle/20171128/city-quotient-sciotos-storybook-statues |accessdate=October 22, 2018 |work=Columbus Monthly |date=November 28, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Battelle Riverfront Park |url=http://www.sciotomile.com/parks/batelle-riverfront-park/ |publisher=Columbus Recreation and Parks Department |accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref> The grove is named after Jim Barney, who served as director of the Columbus Recreation and Parks Department, and the sculptures were relocated to their current location in 2015.<ref name=Darbee/>
The figures, sometimes collectively referred to as '''''Children's Fountain''''', '''''KidSpeak Children's Fountain''''', or '''''Pickaweekee Children's Fountain''''', include '''''Eagle''''',<ref>{{cite web |title=Eagle, (sculpture). |url=https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!315376~!0#focus |publisher=[[Smithsonian Institution]] |accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref> '''''Griffin''''',<ref>{{cite web |title=Griffin, (sculpture). |url=https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!315379~!0#focus |publisher=Smithsonian Institution |accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref> '''''Hound''''',<ref>{{cite web |title=Hound, (sculpture). |url=https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!315378~!0#focus |publisher=Smithsonian Institution |accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref> '''''Lion''''',<ref>{{cite web |title=Lion, (sculpture). |url=https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!315380~!0#focus |publisher=Smithsonian Institution |accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref> '''''Owl''''',<ref>{{cite web |title=Owl, (sculpture). |url=https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!315381~!0#focus |publisher=Smithsonian Institution |accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref> and '''''Unicorn'''''.<ref name=Darbee/><ref>{{cite web |title=Unicorn, (sculpture). |url=https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!315377~!0#focus |publisher=Smithsonian Institution |accessdate=October 22, 2018}}</ref>
